FBIS4-42306 "drweu106_g_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 CANADA Cote d'Ivoire's $60 Million Debt Written Off Cote d'Ivoire's $60 Million Debt Written Off LD0106153894 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 1330 GMT 1 Jun 94 LD0106153894 Montreal Radio Canada International English BFN [Text] The Canadian Embassy in Abidjan says Ottawa has forgiven the West African country of the Ivory Coast a debt of 60 million dollars U.S., and (?a) statement says another 60 million dollars in debt will be rescheduled. Ivory Coast has a total foreign debt of 21 billion dollars, the highest per capita in the world.
